    "description": "Nalco is actively seeking a talented and motivated Process Engineer to join our dynamic team in Vadodara. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Nalco:\nNalco is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in Root Cause Analysis\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Referral bonus program\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vadodara, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Nalco!",
